We recommended that Management require the Municipal Budget Officer to:

Prepare the budgets in conformity with the budgetary laws and rules;


Avoid appropriating lump sum amounts and specify the object of expenditures;

Immediately observe recommendations or exceptions noted by the SP during the budget review; and



Comply with the pending request of SP to break down lump sum budgets on the items under MOOE for FY 2016 to facilitate the latter’s review thereof, otherwise, we will issue ND for making disbursements out of appropriations not reviewed and approved by the SP.

Strictly comply with the requirements of the NBC No. 466-A to ensure propriety and necessity in procuring second-hand vehicles.  Such procurement should always be in line with the State’s policy of optimizing the utilization of public resources and the enhancement of economy in government operations;
Explain and provide justification on their non-compliance with important provisions of above NBC; and
Submit the required certification or documentation for the transaction in order to avoid future suspension in audit.

Submit a valid justification for our review/evaluation why the usual process of procurement of goods/services such as meals/snacks were not made instead of releasing directly to individual participants the allocation for meals/snacks or catering services;
Submit the required documentation for the transaction in order to avoid future suspension in audit; and
Strictly adhere with the provisions of IRR of R.A. No. 9184.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Budget Officer to:


Prepare the budgets in conformity with the budgetary laws and rules;


Avoid appropriating lump sum amounts and specify the object of expenditures;

Immediately observe recommendations or exceptions noted by the SP during the budget review; and



Comply with the pending request of SP to break down lump sum budgets on the items under Maintenance and Other Operating Expenses (MOOE) for Fiscal Year (FY) 2016 to facilitate the latter’s review thereof, otherwise, we will issue Notices of Disallowance (ND) for making disbursements out of appropriations not reviewed and approved by the SP.
